Virtual address layout in:

32-bit:
-------
	
	,-------------------------------------------------------,
	|  pgd  |     pmd	|      pte	|      off	|
	*-------------------------------------------------------*

bits:  31 <-> 30|29  <------> 21|20  <------> 12|11  <------>	0

	offset	:  0-11 bits	(12 bits)
	pte	: 12-20	bits	(9  bits)
	pmd	: 21-29 bits	(9  bits)
	pud	: always rounded to 0. (0 bits)
	pgd	: 30-31 bits	(2  bits)


To get offset from given virtual address of 32-bit(4bytes):

	offset_val=((vaddr<<(31-11))>>(31-11));
		/* ie., vaddr=vaddr<<(31-11);vaddr=vaddr>>(31-11); */



64-bit:
-------

	,-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------,
        |    reserved    |      pgd	|      pud	|     pmd       |      pte      |      off      |
        *-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*

bits:  63  <-------->  48|47 <------> 39|38  <------> 30|29  <------> 21|20  <------> 12|11  <------->  0      	

        offset  :  0-11 bits    (12 bits)
        pte     : 12-20 bits    (9  bits)
        pmd     : 21-29 bits    (9  bits)
        pud     : 30-38 bits	(9  bits)
        pgd     : 39-47 bits    (9  bits)
	reserved: 48-63 bits	(16 bits)
              
To get offset from given virtual address of 64-bit(8bytes):

        offset_val=((vaddr<<(63-11))>>(63-11));
                /* ie., vaddr=vaddr<<(63-11);vaddr=vaddr>>(63-11); */




